FBIS3-19267 "drweu050_j_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-050 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Mar 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Ciampi: Need for European Political Structures LD1403200894 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 1845 GMT 14 Mar 94 LD1403200894 Rome RAI Due Television Network Language: Italian Article Type:BFN [Text] Prime Minister Carlo Azegio Ciampi, speaking at the Institute of International Affairs, touched upon the topics of the G-7 and the crisis in Europe. He said that Italy is working to ensure that Russia will participate more fully at the next meeting of G-7, which will be held in Naples. The prime minister added that the crisis in Yugoslavia is proof of a lack of a common European defense and security policy. Ciampi also warned that political integration must make progress in order to overcome recent setbacks. He said that without political structures, Europe is putting its future evolution at risk.
